<HEADLINE>
FT  17 JUL 92 / Executive ousted from TV network
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By RAYMOND SNODDY
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
MR Francis Baron, chief executive of the European Television Networks (ETN),
the former satellite television division of WH Smith, has been ousted from
his job.
Mr Baron had been responsible since 1984 for WH Smith's foray into
television until last year, when the cable and satellite channels were sold
to Capital Cities/ABC of the US, and Canal Plus and Compagnie Generale des
Eaux.
There have been disagreements about the direction of the company, with
important decisions being delayed. It is believed that Mr Baron called a
shareholders' meeting on Tuesday to try to resolve the deadlock.
One issue is likely to have been Mr Baron's fight to win equal access to
television sporting rights.
There was also a difference of approach on strategy. Mr Baron has pioneered
the creation of a pan-European network of sports channels. Canal Plus, the
subscription television channel, has tended to expand by setting up separate
ventures in individual nations.
Mr Richard Spinner, an executive of Capital Cities/ABC, and senior
vice-president and managing director of CC/ABC's European operations, has
taken over as chief executive of ETN.
</TEXT>
