<HEADLINE>
FT  17 JUL 92 / FT Quarterly Review of Personal Finance (15): How this
exercise works
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
This feature is not a competition but an allocation exercise. The purpose is
to see how four professional fund managers manage a Pounds 250,000 portfolio
on behalf of a hypothetical client of their choice.
In each case, the client is assumed to be either a wealthy individual or a
small self-administered pension fund; and all four emphasise that they are
investing for the long term (10 years or more) rather than for short-term
gain.
The exercise started at the beginning of October 1990. The portfolios given
here were drawn up as at the beginning of this month, and will be reviewed
at the end of September.
</TEXT>
