FT  17 JUL 92 / International Company News: Ricoh buys French distributor
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By EMIKO TERAZONO
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   TOKYO
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
RICOH, the Japanese office equipment manufacturer, yesterday announced that
it would acquire SMO Bureautique, a distribution subsidiary of Metrologie
International, the French electrical equipment company.
Ricoh's Fr202.5m (Dollars 49m) purchase follows that by Canon, another
Japanese office supply maker, in establishing independent manufacturing and
distribution operations in France.
The move comes at a time when Japanese companies are refocusing their
investments towards core domestic businesses. Overseas acquisitions by
Japanese companies have declined sharply as the fall in the stock and real
estate markets have squeezed companies' cash flow.
Ricoh said the move was strategically important, as a quarter of its sales
in Europe was generated in France. Its production line in Colmar, Alsace,
has been manufacturing photocopiers, facsimile machines and other office
equipment since 1987.
Ricoh said there would be no drastic restructuring of operations at SMO
Bureautique, which employs over 800 staff.
</TEXT>
