FT  17 JUL 92 / International Company News: Canadian gold merger nearer
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ROBERT GIBBENS
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   MONTREAL
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
THE merger of Homestake Mining with Canada's International Corona to form
North America's largest gold producer has only one step to go, writes Robert
Gibbens in Montreal.
Homestake's shareholders in San Francisco approved the USDollars 400m share
exchange offer. It requires approval of 90 per cent of Corona's shareholders
by July 22.
