<HEADLINE>
FT  17 JUL 92 / Arts: Today's Television
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By CHRISTOPHER DUNKLEY
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
ONCE again we arrive at The First Night Of The Proms. The 98th season begins
with a live relay from the Albert Hall (7.30 Radio 3 and BBC2) of Verdi's
Requiem. Andrew Davis conducts the BBC Symphony Orchestra, the BBC Singers,
the London Symphony Chorus and the BBC Symphony Chorus, and an international
band of soloists led by Susan Dunn.
It looks like Mavis Nicholson benefit night, and why not? Channel 4 begins
evening repeats of her daytime programmes. In With Mavis (8.30) starts with
an interview about Alzheimer's disease. Then at 10.00 the estimable
Nicholson presents the 2-hour Radio 2 Arts Programme which features Meredith
Edwards talking about his career in films.
It looks as though Nick Utechin, the new producer of Any Questions, is doing
the business: at the time of writing, his panel contains not a single MP,
which is what listeners so often plead for (8.05 Radio 4). BBC2 repeats Alan
Bennett's award-winning drama A Question Of Attribution, featuring Anthony
Blunt and the Queen, played by Prunella Scales.
