<HEADLINE>
FT  16 JUL 92 / UK Company News: Williams expands components side
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Williams Holdings, the international conglomerate, has acquired the building
components division of Charles Baynes, the Surrey-based specialist engineer,
for Pounds 8.6m cash.
The division, which comprises Ancon Stainless Steel Fixings, Ancon Couplers
(MBT) and Harris &amp; Edgar, achieved combined turnover of Pounds 12.2m and
operating profits of Pounds 600,000 in the 1991 year. Net assets at
completion will amount to Pounds 1.5m.
