<HEADLINE>
FT  16 JUL 92 / UK Company News: Kalon bid referral is urged
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By DAVID OWEN
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
MR MICHAEL Heseltine, president of the board of trade, was yesterday urged
to refer Kalon's hostile all-paper bid for Manders (Holdings), its
Wolverhampton-based paint-making rival, to the Monopolies and Mergers
Commission in a parliamentary early day motion signed by 49 MPs.
Signatories included Ms Marjorie Mowlam, Labour's front bench spokeswoman on
City affairs, Mr Richard Caborn, Labour chairman of the all-party select
committee on trade and industry, and Mr Nicholas Budgen, Tory MP for
Wolverhampton South West.
Noting that a takeover would give Kalon more than 70 per cent of the
own-label paint market, the motion argues that a merger would 'threaten a
reduction in competition against the public interest.'
Kalon's objective is 'to achieve an increased market share of the paint
market, and in the process cut 500 jobs from the workforce of a combined
group,' the motion states.
</TEXT>
